The paper discusses security issues in peer-to-peer networks, which are primarily related to computer networks (cs.NI) and security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses attacks on the network, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper reviews protection mechanisms, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE).
